PGDipLP is an acronym for Post Graduate Diploma in Legal Practice. It is often used after the names of those who have studied and passed the [[Legal Practice Course]]. It is mostly used by those who have not yet attained [[Solicitor]] status or who may not necessarily intend to become solicitors.<br /><br />An alternative is DipLP.<br /><br />[[User:Joerv007|Joerv007]] 07:59, 17 August 2007 (UTC)